events.name: Houston Rockets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 24 points, Dejounte Murray had 18 points and 10 rebounds and the San Antonio Spurs rallied to beat the undermanned Houston Rockets 103-91 on Saturday, snapping a four-game home losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs end 4-game home skid, top short-handed Rockets 103-91

headlines.description: — James Harden delivered 32 points and a triple-double in his Brooklyn debut, Kevin Durant scored a season-high 42 points in his first game back with his former teammate, and the Nets showed off their potent potential in a 122-115 victory over the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden debuts with triple-double, Durant scores 42, Nets win

headlines.description: — The Detroit Pistons had their most dominant quarter in nearly two years. And last season’s NBA Finals trip for the Miami Heat suddenly seems long ago.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons come into Miami and roll past reeling Heat, 120-100

headlines.description: — Ja Morant returned to the Memphis lineup after missing eight games with an ankle injury and scored 17 points, leading the Grizzlies to a 106-104 win over the Philadelphia 76ers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant returns, Grizzlies top 76ers 106-104 for 4th straight

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 36 points and the Portland Trail Blazers rebounded from a first-half deficit to beat the Atlanta Hawks 112-106 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard helps Blazers rally for a 112-106 win over Hawks
